      "content": "hey, i'm working on this tool for our legal team in brussels to pull out mandatory requirements from GDPR-style docs. i need a python function `extract_requirements(text: str) -> list[str]` that identifies the specific regulatory obligations.\n\nhere is the sample text I'm working with:\n\"The controller shall implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to ensure a level of security appropriate to the risk. Data protection officers must be designated when processing involves regular and systematic monitoring of data subjects on a large scale.\"\n\nfor this specific text, i need it to return exactly:\n['implement appropriate technical and organizational measures', 'designated when processing involves regular and systematic monitoring']\n\ncan u write the function? i'll run it against a few test cases to make sure it's calibrated right.",
